===============================================================
*U**niversity Degree in Terminology – Online training - Opening in 
January 2023*
===============================================================
https://du.condillac.org/Home-en
Courses online in English
Opening in January 2023

The University of Savoie Mont-Blanc in partnership with the Nova 
University of Lisbon and in collaboration with the University of 
Grenoble and the Terminology Coordination Unit of the DG Translation of 
the European Parliament, is offering a University Diploma on the 
"Foundations and Challenges of Terminology".

This training aims to equip everyone with the skills needed to:
– Manage and define concepts and terms;
– Capitalise on and transmit knowledge;
– Contribute to the management of multilingualism;
– Organise technical communication.

The 112-hour course consists of 2 blocks of compulsory skills, 1 basic 
block and a block of optional specialisation: "Terminology applied to 
translation in a professional context" and/or "Terminology in the 
digital age"

_Target audience_: Terminologists, Translators, Linguists, Engineers, 
Documentalists, HR managers, Lawyers, Healthcare professionals, Quality 
assurance officers, Technicians...

_Key lecturers_:
- Christophe Roche, Professor at the University of Savoie Mont-Blanc, 
President of the AFNOR Terminology Commission (X03A).
- Costa Rute, Professor, President of the Centre of Linguistics of the 
NOVA University of Lisboa (CLUNL);
- Candel Danielle, Associate member of the CNRS laboratory “Histoire des 
théories linguistiques”, University Paris Cité, Linguist expert in 
official Terminology;
- Frérot Cécile, Senior Lecturer at the University of Grenoble Alpes, 
Head of the LEA Masters in Multilingual Specialised Translation, 
University of Grenoble Alpes, member of the ILCEA4 laboratory;
- Maslias Rodolfo, Head of the Terminology Coordination Unit of the DG 
Translation of the European Parliament, European Parliament 
representative in the IATE Interinstitutional Management Group;

_Booklet and Pre-registration_: 
https://www.univ-smb.fr/formation-continue/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2021/06/university-degree-in-foundations-and-challenges-of-terminology-iufp-usmb.pdf

Prof Christophe ROCHE

Condillac Research Group - LISTIC Lab.
Université Savoie Mont-Blanc - Campus Scientifique
73376 Le Bourget du Lac cedex - France

christophe.roche@univ-savoie.fr
